Response bias: This occurs when respondents do not answer questions truthfully or accurately due to social desirability, fear of reprisal, or other reasons.
Measurement error: This occurs when the questions or scale used to measure attitudes are not properly constructed or validated, leading to inaccurate or unreliable results.
Self-report bias: This occurs when the person providing the attitude data is not the person whose attitudes are being measured, leading to inaccurate or unreliable results.
